<p class="">I think that the bulk of this House will agree that these two gentlemen have discharged their very difficult offices pretty well. Secondly, I think it must be agreed that they have shown a very quick absorption of the manners of life in this House, which is something which very few people who have been in the House a great deal longer would say they did not envy. The right hon. and gallant Member for Gainsborough, who is certainly guilty of having been ungenerous, <span id="980" class="column-number" data-column-number="980"></span> should not have sought to depreciate the Law Officers and the Committee of Privileges at the same time.<p></p> The Opposition are attacking the appointment of two hon. Gentlemen to the Committee of Privileges. I sincerely hope that we have heard the last of this rather ungenerous intervention and that we shall leave the Committee of Privileges still commanding the respect of the House and the country.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
